parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, swerve, or fail to stop, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes lock up during turns
the vehicle pulls severely to one side
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes slip before stopping the vehicle fully
the brake rotors separate from the hub while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of brake rotors can cause them to fail, leading to brake system failure, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The brake rotors corrode and fail
the vehicle pulls severely to one side
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes slip before stopping the vehicle fully.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Tread separation
tire blowout
shaking or vibration while driving
loss of vehicle control
cracks on the sidewall or tread area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure due to cracking can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Cracks on the sidewall or tread area
tire blowout
shaking or vibration while driving
loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat and seatbelt system can cause injuries, including whiplash and back strain, due to the seats unlocking and sliding around while driving, and the seatbelts fraying and failing to provide proper restraint.
symptoms: The seats unlock and slide around while driving
the seatbelts fail to hold the driver and passengers in place
the seatbelts fray and break
the seatbelt buckle alarm actuator is broken
the driver cannot buckle the seatbelt or receives a false sense of buckling.
